== Access ==
[[File:NaraPrefRoad155.JPG|thumb|Prefectural Route 155, with a sign urging caution for pedestrians.]]
For those traveling by car, access was previously limited to ascending from the Sakurai side via {{ill|Nara Prefectural Route 37|ja|奈良県道37号桜井吉野線|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara Prefectural Route 37|1=Nara Prefectural Road Route 37|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11445381}}. This route included many narrow, single-lane sections, causing severe congestion during the autumn foliage season. However, the Completion tier 6]]

{{translated page|ja|多武峰|version=100113511|comment=Imported full ja history}}

 in 2009 significantly improved access from the Asuka area. Nonetheless, this road intersects several hiking trails, including one leading from the {{ill|Ishibutai Kofun|en|Ishibutai Kofun|qid=Q3816159|lt=Ishibutai Kofun|1=Ishibutai Kofun}}, necessitating careful driving. Parking at Tōnomine remains limited, so visitors are advised to use public transportation (buses from {{ill|Sakurai Station|en|Sakurai Station|qid=Q1205698|lt=Sakurai Station (Nara)|1=Sakurai Station}}) or hike (approximately 1.5–2 hours from Ishibutai Kofun).

